{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Util/UnusedBinders.html#Lean.Expr.hasUnusedForallBindersWhere\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Expr</span>.<span class=\"name\">hasUnusedForallBindersWhere</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">p</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.BinderInfo\">BinderInfo</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">e</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Bool\">Bool</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Tests if any of the binders of `(x₀ : A₀) → (x₁ : A₁) → ⋯ → X` which satisfy `p Aᵢ bi` (with `bi`\nthe `binderInfo`) are unused in the renainder of the type (i.e. in `(xᵢ₊₁ : Aᵢ₊₁) → ⋯ → X`).\n\nNote that the argument to `p` may have loose bvars. This is a performance optimization.\n\nThis function runs `cleanupAnnotations` on each type suffix `(xᵢ₊₁ : Aᵢ₊₁) → ⋯ → X` before\nexamining it.\n\nWe see through `let`s, and do not report if any of them are unused.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Util/UnusedBinders.html#Lean.Expr.hasUnusedForallBindersWhere","kind":"opaque","line":15,"name":"Lean.Expr.hasUnusedForallBindersWhere","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Util/UnusedBinders.lean#L15-L33"}}],"imports":["Lean.Expr"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Util.UnusedBinders"}